2012年4月28日焚烧古兰经事件发生后，琼斯因违反消防安全规定被盖恩斯维尔消防救援队罚款271美元（如先前奧巴馬所言）。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Pastor burns holy books in protest of imprisoned clergyman|url=https://www.gainesville.com/article/20120428/News/604136019|accessdate=2021-04-07|last=writer|first=Cindy SwirkoStaff|work=Gainesville Sun|language=en}}{{Dead link}}</ref>

=== 迪尔伯恩 ===
琼斯计划于2011年4月在[[美国伊斯兰中心|美国伊斯兰中心]]外举行抗议活动。但在他要参加抗议活动的当天，地方当局在法庭上就对他进行询问并以“破壞和平”爲由将其起訴。法庭要求琼斯交纳4.5万美元的“和平保证金”以支付極端分子在集會上攻击瓊斯的“事前費用”，要么接受审判，而琼斯对这一要求提出异议。經陪审团于4月22日投票表決要求他交纳1美元的象徵性「和平保证金」，但琼斯和他的合作牧师韦恩·萨普仍然拒绝交纳。於是他们被短暂地收押，此期間他們稱這侵犯了第一修正案賦予美國公民的权利。当天晚上，琼斯被法院判决無罪释放。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Jones Released from Jail After Paying 'Peace Bond' - Fox 2 News Headlines|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130702110254/http://www.myfoxdetroit.com/story/18461890/jones-released-from-jail-after-paying-peace-bond|accessdate=2021-04-07|date=2013-07-02|work=web.archive.org}}</ref>[[美國公民自由聯盟|美国公民自由联盟]]（ACLU）曾提交了一份支持琼斯抗议计划的非当事人意见陈述书。<ref name="#11">{{Cite web|title=Judge vacates 'breach of peace' judgement against Terry Jones|url=https://www.mlive.com/news/detroit/2011/11/judge_vacates_breach_of_peace.html|accessdate=2021-04-07|date=2011-11-11|work=mlive|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307212522/https://www.mlive.com/news/detroit/2011/11/judge_vacates_breach_of_peace.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2011年11月11日，韦恩县巡回法院法官[[罗伯特·齐奥尔科夫斯基|罗伯特·齐奥尔科夫斯基]]撤销了对琼斯和韦恩·萨普的「破坏和平」裁决，理由是裁判程序違反[[程序正义|程序正義]]。<ref name="#11"/><ref>{{Cite web|title="Stand Up America Now, Wayne Sapp and Terry Jones v. City of Dearborn and Ronald Haddad" (PDF). Thomasmore.org. Retrieved 2015-07-14.|url=http://www.thomasmore.org/sites/default/files/files/Order-Opinion%20Granting%20Summary%20Judgment%281%29.pdf|access-date=2021-04-07|archive-date=2021-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210223170005/http://www.thomasmore.org/sites/default/files/files/Order-Opinion%20Granting%20Summary%20Judgment(1).pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 加拿大 ===
2012年10月11日，琼斯原计划在[[加拿大|加拿大]]参加一场关于言论自由的辩论会，但因之前在密歇根州迪尔伯恩的违法行为及20年前德国政府曾因他使用冒名使用「博士」头衔而对其进行過罚款，而被[[加拿大政府|加拿大政府]]拒绝入境。然而早在2011年11月，琼斯在迪尔伯恩的违法指控就因被质疑而被推翻，且琼斯被证实确实拥有[[名誉学位|荣誉博士]]学位，但加拿大政府在没有案件文件的情况下仍拒绝其入境，实际上是禁止他參加該活动。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Quran-Burning Pastor's Jailing Raises First Amendment Questions|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/terry-jones-jailed-michigan_n_852916|accessdate=2021-04-07|date=2011-04-23|last=Knafo|first=Saki|work=HuffPost|language=en|archive-date=2021-05-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210508140110/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/terry-jones-jailed-michigan_n_852916|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thomasmore.org/press-releases/2011/11/victory-pastor-jones-court-rules-pastor-s-constitutional-rights-were-violated |title=Victory for Pastor Jones; Court Rules that Pastor's Constitutional Rights Were Violated by "Peace Bond" Trial|access-date=2013-06-07 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120622215711/http://www.thomasmore.org/press-releases/2011/11/victory-pastor-jones-court-rules-pastor-s-constitutional-rights-were-violated |archive-date=2012-06-22 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Koran-burning U.S. pastor barred from entering Canada for debate|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/11/us-jones-blocked-idUSBRE89A1MA20121011|publisher=Reuters|access-date=2012-10-11|first=Russ|last=Blinch|date=2012-10-11|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924171240/http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/11/us-jones-blocked-idUSBRE89A1MA20121011|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>[http://news.nationalpost.com/2012/10/11/koran-burning-pastor-terry-jones-barred-from-canada-for-anti-muslim-film-debate/ Koran-burning pastor Terry Jones barred from Canada for anti-Muslim film debate] by Stewart Bell, ''[[国家邮报|National Post]]'', 2012-10-11.</ref>

